entry.title: Order in Council dated 5 November 1926, approving regulations as to Prize Money Accounts (1926)
Order in Council as to registration of ships of the Government of the Straits Settlements (1926)
Order in Council (No 26) Relating to Picric Acid, Picrates and Mixtures of Picric Acid with other substances (1926)
Coastguard Act 1925
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law with respect to the Coastguard, and for the purposes connected therewith.

entry.title: Diocesan Boards of Finance Measure 1925
entry.summary: A Measure passed by the National Assembly of the Church of England To make provision for the Powers, Duties and Constitution of Diocesan Boards of Finance.

entry.title: Land Settlement (Facilities) Amendment Act 1925 (repealed 5.11.1993)
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Land Settlement (Facilities) Act, 1919, by substituting other provisions for those contained in section twenty-seven of the said Act.

entry.title: Rating and Valuation Act 1925
entry.summary: An Act to simplify and amend the law with respect to the making and collection of rates by the consolidation of rates and otherwise, to promote uniformity in the valuation of property for the purpose of rates, to amend the law with respect to the valuation of machinery and certain other classes of properties, and for other purposes incidental to or connected with the matters aforesaid.

entry.title: Criminal Justice Act 1925
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law with respect to the administration of criminal justice in England, and otherwise to amend the criminal law.

entry.title: Tithe Act 1925 (repealed 19.11.1998)
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law relating to tithe rentcharge and other rentcharges, rents and payments in lieu of tithe, and the payment of rates thereon; and for other matters connected therewith.

entry.title: Honours (Prevention of Abuses) Act 1925
entry.summary: An Act for the prevention of abuses in connection with the Grant of Honours

entry.title: National Library of Scotland Act 1925
entry.summary: An Act to establish a National Library in Scotland on the foundation of the Library gifted for that purpose by the Faculty of Advocates, and for purposes connected therewith.

entry.title: Allotments Act 1925
entry.summary: An Act to facilitate the acquisition and maintenance of allotments, and to make further provision for the security of tenure of tenants of allotments.

entry.title: Public Health Act 1925
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Public Health Acts 1875 to 1907, and the Baths and Washhouses Acts 1846 to 1899, in respect of matters for which provision is commonly made in local Acts and for other purposes relating to the public health.

entry.title: Merchant Shipping (International Labour Conventions) Act 1925 (repealed 1.5.1995)
entry.summary: An Act to give effect to certain Draft Conventions adopted by the International Labour Conference relating respectively to an unemployment indemnity for seamen in the case of loss or foundering of their ship, the minimum age for the admission of young persons to employment as trimmers and stokers, and the compulsory medical examination of children and young persons employed at sea.

entry.title: Merchant Shipping (Equivalent Provisions) Act 1925 (repealed 1.5.1994)
entry.summary: An Act to provide for the exemption, in certain circumstances, of Foreign ships and British ships registered outside the United Kingdom from certain provisions of the Merchant Shipping Acts.
